'''Cwm''' is a village and [[community (Wales)|community]] in [[Denbighshire]], below the hill [[Mynydd y Cwm]].

The church in Cwm is dedicated to two 6th century saints, [[St Mael]] and [[St Sulie]]n.<ref name="church St Mael">{{cite web|last=CPAT|title=Church of St Mael and St Sulien , Cwm|url=http://www.cpat.demon.co.uk/projects/longer/churches/denbigh/16756.htm|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref>

Local councillors have given the go ahead for a wind turbine to be erected on farmland near Cwm. The 50&nbsp;kW turbine will be at Marian Mawr and it was voted through with a big majority by [[Denbighshire County Council]].<ref name=Turbines>{{cite web|last=Foregrave|first=Andrew|title=Cwm turbine row: Denbighshire residents fear 'colonisation' by wind farms|url=http://www.dailypost.co.uk/news/north-wales-news/cwm-wind-farm-residents-anger-2994247|work=Daily Post|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref>

